  "local_port": 51050,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you make an at home weight loss wrap?",
  "response": "Creating a healthy, homemade weight loss wrap is a delicious and nutritious way to support your weight management goals. Below is a simple recipe that incorporates lean proteins, fresh vegetables, and whole grains to help keep you satisfied while providing essential nutrients.\n\n### **Ingredients:**\n\n- **Whole Wheat or Low-Carb Tortillas:**\n  - Choose whole wheat, spinach, or other whole-grain tortillas for added fiber and nutrients.\n\n- **Lean Protein:**\n  - 3-4 oz of grilled chicken breast, turkey slices, tofu, or chickpeas.\n\n- **Fresh Vegetables:**\n  - 1/2 cup mixed greens (spinach, kale, or lettuce)\n  - 1/4 cup sliced cucumbers\n  - 1/4 cup diced tomatoes\n  - 1/4 cup shredded carrots\n  - 1/4 avocado, sliced (optional for healthy fats)\n\n- **Healthy Fats:**\n  - 1-2 tablespoons hummus, Greek yogurt, or a light vinaigrette dressing.\n\n- **Additional Flavorings (Optional):**\n  - Sliced red onions\n  - Fresh herbs (like cilantro or basil)\n  - Squeeze of lemon or lime juice\n  - Black pepper or your favorite spices\n\n### **Instructions:**\n\n1. **Prepare the Protein:**\n   - If using chicken or turkey, grill or bake the breast until fully cooked. Let it rest for a few minutes, then slice into thin strips.\n   - For vegetarian options, rinse and drain chickpeas or prepare tofu by marinating and lightly saut\u00e9ing until golden.\n\n2. **Warm the Tortilla:**\n   - Gently warm the tortilla in a dry skillet over medium heat for about 30 seconds on each side or microwave it for about 15-20 seconds to make it more pliable.\n\n3. **Assemble the Wrap:**\n   - Lay the warmed tortilla flat on a clean surface.\n   - Spread a thin layer of hummus or Greek yogurt in the center of the tortilla. This acts as a healthy spread that adds flavor and moisture.\n   - Layer the mixed greens evenly over the spread.\n\n4. **Add the Fillings:**\n   - Place your chosen protein (chicken, turkey, tofu, etc.) on top of the greens.\n   - Add the sliced cucumbers, diced tomatoes, shredded carrots, and avocado slices.\n   - Sprinkle any additional flavorings like red onions or fresh herbs.\n\n5. **Dress the Wrap:**\n   - Drizzle a small amount of light vinaigrette or squeeze fresh lemon/lime juice over the fillings for extra flavor without adding excessive calories.\n   - Season with black pepper or your favorite spices to taste.\n\n6. **Roll the Wrap:**\n   - Fold in the sides of the tortilla slightly, then roll it tightly from the bottom up, ensuring all fillings are securely enclosed.\n\n7. **Serve:**\n   - Cut the wrap in half diagonally for easier handling and serve immediately.\n   - Enjoy it with a side of fresh veggies, a light soup, or a piece of fruit for a complete meal.\n\n### **Tips for a Weight Loss-Friendly Wrap:**\n\n- **Portion Control:** Be mindful of portion sizes, especially with higher-calorie ingredients like avocados and dressings.\n- **Fiber-Rich Ingredients:** Incorporate plenty of vegetables and whole grains to increase fiber intake, which can help keep you full longer.\n- **Lean Proteins:** Opt for lean protein sources to build muscle mass and support metabolism.\n- **Healthy Fats:** Include sources of healthy fats, such as avocados or hummus, but use them in moderation.\n- **Limit Added Sugars and Sodium:** Choose ingredients with lower added sugars and sodium to keep the wrap healthier.\n- **Customize to Taste:** Feel free to adjust the ingredients to suit your preferences and dietary needs.\n\n### **Example Wrap Combination:**\n\n**Grilled Chicken & Veggie Wrap**\n\n- **Tortilla:** Whole wheat\n- **Protein:** Grilled chicken breast\n- **Vegetables:** Mixed greens, sliced cucumbers, diced tomatoes, shredded carrots, avocado\n- **Spread:** Hummus\n- **Extras:** Fresh cilantro, squeeze of lime juice, black pepper\n\nThis combination offers a balanced mix of protein, fiber, and healthy fats, making it a satisfying and nutritious option for a weight loss-friendly meal.\n\n### **Final Thoughts:**\n\nPreparing wraps at home allows you to control the ingredients and tailor the meal to your nutritional needs and taste preferences. Experiment with different proteins, vegetables, and spreads to keep your meals interesting and enjoyable while working towards your weight loss goals.",
